"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody. This is my compost pile, and this is how I'm gonna change the world with it. And when I mean the world, maybe just my backyard, but that's enough of the world for me. So the idea behind my compost pile is I'm creating soil. I'm taking waste product from my kitchen, my commercial kitchen that I produce a ton of waste product from. I take some leaves that I get from my neighbor's driveways, I mix them together, add a little bit of water, and then every day I pitch it. And this is kind of my little relaxing moment where I get outside, I generally wait till it's a little bit cooler, and do about my five minutes worth of nice exercise towards making some good healthy soil from our garden. The little bugs that we can't see, the bacteria and what have you that give us problems with our food and everything else. And then we're safe. And we are. They're right, but there's something that's begins to become evident that we're missing. We are living creatures, and we need living substances. And these little bugs, this single cell life that is covering everything, it's maintaining it in a way that we're only now beginning to understand. And so I feel that this sterilization that we're doing, and we're doing it with our farming, we're doing it with our cities, we're doing it with our guts, we're doing with everything is a real negative. And I think it's gonna give everybody some form of gut disassociation, is what I call it, but really an autoimmune disorder. A system where the body is healing itself to death, or at least to further sickness, where the immune system that's handled by the gut is no longer connected in a healthy way to the membrane, which is you, and it's healing it in ways that are detrimental to the membrane's overall health. It's the body making itself sick, the immune system turned against healthy tissue, and this is an epidemic where in America and elsewhere, Western diets and cultures where we do sterilize everything because o